            <li><span class="li-icon">→</span><span><strong>Hidden coupling.</strong> Consumers depend on a global implicitly, making dependencies invisible in signatures.</span></li>
            <li><span class="li-icon">→</span><span><strong>Violates SRP.</strong> The class manages both its own logic and its own lifecycle (instance control).</span></li>
            <li><span class="li-icon">→</span><span><strong>Concurrency risks.</strong> In multi-threaded environments, race conditions can create multiple instances without careful locking.</span></li>
            <li><span class="li-icon">→</span><span><strong>Lifetime management.</strong> The instance lives for the entire app lifetime, which may waste memory if rarely used.</span></li>
