          all of them becomes thousands of characters long and nearly unmaintainable.
        </span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="bullet">💬</span>
        <span>
          <strong>Comments are legal.</strong> Addresses like
          <code>user(comment)@example.com</code> and
          <code>(comment)user@example.com</code> are technically valid per RFC 5322,
          but almost no regex handles them correctly.
        </span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="bullet">🔤</span>
        <span>
          <strong>Quoted local parts.</strong> <code>"user name"@example.com</code>
          and <code>"very.unusual.@.unusual.com"@example.com</code> are both valid.
          Regex struggles to correctly parse the quoting rules.
        </span>
