<span class="comment">// WHERE name LIKE '%' OR '1'='1%'</span>
<span class="comment">// → Returns ALL rows! 💀</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h4 style="color:#68d391; margin-bottom:12px; font-size:1em;">🛡️ Safe — Parameterized Queries</h4>
                <div class="steps">
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number green">1</div>
                        <div class="step-content green">
                            <h5>Query structure defined first</h5>
                            <p>The SQL template is written with placeholders (<code style="color:#68d391">?</code> or <code style="color:#68d391">$1</code>) before any user input is involved.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="step">
                        <div class="step-number green">2</div>
                        <div class="step-content green">
                            <h5>Input passed as a separate parameter</h5>
                            <p>User input is never concatenated into the query. The database driver handles binding safely.</p>
