        <h4>A Pragmatic Middle Ground</h4>
        <p>ES6 modules are singletons by nature — the module cache ensures one instance. Exporting a plain object or a frozen config from a module gives you singleton semantics without a class, and it's far easier to mock in tests.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
