        <p style="font-size:0.9rem; color:var(--text-secondary);">
          <strong style="color:var(--accent);">Bottom line:</strong>
          The Singleton pattern is a tool, not a rule. Ask yourself: <em>"Would this be hard to test?"</em>
          and <em>"Does a consumer need to know about this dependency?"</em>
          If either answer is yes, reach for dependency injection or a framework-managed store instead.
          If the resource is genuinely global, stateless, and never needs mocking, a Singleton
          (or better yet, a simple ES6 module export) is perfectly reasonable.
        </p>
