        Recursion depth is the number of times a function calls <em>itself</em> before
        reaching a base case and returning.  Each call is a new stack frame pushed onto
        the <strong>call stack</strong> — a fixed-size region of memory managed by the
        JavaScript engine (and virtually every other runtime).
