---

Here's every problem caught and fixed:

| # | Original | Problem(s) | Fix |
|---|----------|-----------|-----|
| 1 | `GET /getUsers` | Verb in URL; resource not pluralised | `GET /users` |
| 2 | `POST /user/delete/5` | Wrong method for deletion; verb embedded in path; singular resource name | `DELETE /users/5` |
| 3 | `GET /createUser?name=Jo` | GET must be idempotent/safe — never mutates; verb in URL; data in query string instead of body | `POST /users` with JSON body |
| 4 | `PUT /updateAllUsers` | Verb in URL; PUT = full replacement of a single known resource, not bulk partial updates | `PATCH /users` |

The page also includes the complete correct API (GET single, PUT replace, PATCH single) with proper `201` for creation, `204` for deletion, `207` for bulk partial success, and `409` for conflicts — things the original design didn't even consider.

