        <li><span class="fix-icon">✓</span>For updating a <em>single</em> user: <code>PUT /users/{id}</code> (full replace) or <code>PATCH /users/{id}</code> (partial update).</li>
        <li><span class="fix-icon">✓</span>For bulk updates: <code>PATCH /users</code> with a JSON body array is acceptable, but should require explicit IDs in the payload — never an implicit "all".</li>
        <li><span class="fix-icon">✓</span>Consider adding a filter query parameter for scoped bulk updates: <code>PATCH /users?role=admin</code>.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="sub-heading">🚦 Expected Status Codes</div>
