## The Three Leak Sources (summary)

```
Buggy widget lifecycle
──────────────────────
create → bus.on('tick', handler)   ← handler captures DOM node
       → registry.all.push(el)     ← registry holds strong ref
       → setInterval(cb, 500)      ← cb closure captures el

remove → el.remove()               ← DOM gone, but…
       ↳ bus still holds handler   ← el can't be GC'd
       ↳ registry still holds el   ← el can't be GC'd
       ↳ interval still running    ← el can't be GC'd
```

```
Fixed widget lifecycle
──────────────────────
create → store { handler, intervalId } on entry

remove → bus.off('tick', handler)  ← reference released
       → clearInterval(intervalId) ← timer stopped
       → registry.splice(idx, 1)   ← registry ref dropped
       → el.remove()               ← now GC can collect everything ✓
```

The **GC is doing its job perfectly** — it just can't collect objects that your own code is still pointing at. The fix is always in the **teardown path**, not in the garbage collector.

